# Checkout & Payment Gateway Standards

Dokument definiuje twarde standardy dla Medusa checkout i integracji bramek płatniczych. Wszystkie punkty są **OBOWIĄZKOWE** dla nowych projektów. Bazuje na implementacji production-grade z audytu security/stability/compliance.

---

## 1. SECURITY — Bezpieczeństwo

### 1.1 Rate Limiting (MUST)
```typescript
// Backend: apps/backend/src/api/store/custom/*/route.ts
import { Ratelimit } from "@upstash/ratelimit";
import { Redis } from "@upstash/redis";

const ratelimit = new Ratelimit({
  redis: Redis.fromEnv(),
  limiter: Ratelimit.slidingWindow(10, "60s"), // 10 req/min per IP
  prefix: "ratelimit:checkout",
});

const xForwardedFor = req.headers["x-forwarded-for"];
const identifier = (typeof xForwardedFor === "string" ? xForwardedFor : xForwardedFor?.[0]) ?? "anonymous";
const { success, limit, remaining, reset } = await ratelimit.limit(identifier);

if (!success) {
  return res.status(429).json({
    error: "Too many requests",
    limit,
    remaining,
    reset: new Date(reset),
  });
}
```

**Scope**: `/api/store/custom/prepare-checkout`, `/api/store/custom/verify-turnstile`, `/api/store/cart/complete`.

**NEVER**: Nie używaj in-memory rate limitera (ginie przy restart / autoscale). Zawsze Redis (Upstash dla serverless).

